text: Macrozamia conferta is a species of plant in the family Zamiaceae. It is endemic to Queensland, Australia.Bösenberg, J.D. 2010. Macrozamia conferta. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2015.2. Downloaded on 06 September 2015. This species grows in eucalypt woodland habitat. There are 6 or 7 known subpopulations. The species may be threatened by poaching. ==References== conferta Category:Endangered flora of Australia Category:Endangered biota of Queensland Category:Vulnerable flora of Australia Category:Flora of Queensland Category:Nature Conservation Act vulnerable biota Category:Plants described in 1994 Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot Category:Taxa named by Paul Irwin Forster
